    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-03T21:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-03T21:41:00-05:00" n="1214"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.6363/91.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-03T20:00:00-06:41">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>New rate of collecting oil production tax is great benefit to oil companies. The
                    new decree is based on law of June 3, 1912, placing tax at 20 cents per ton, in
                    Mexican gold, allowing exception of paying same in American gold which means New
                    York exchange at rate of two for one. This is big reduction from rate of 75
                    cents, Mexican, charged by Federal Government. Respectfully request instructions
                    relative advising American companies to pay same without protest. In connection
                    with decree for payment oil and customs Charges and taxes, it said that bank
                    currency issued prior to February 19th, 1913, recognized by Constitutionalists
                    as valid but will not be accepted in payment of such Charges.</p>
                <p>Up to present time no demands for loans or war taxes have been made upon American
                    citizens oil companies.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
